1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
I know zero Japanese. I need one table for one.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:19,000
MA starts with one useful phrase, not an empty conversation.

3
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:33,000
The support disappears: full phrase, rhythm, then no answer text.

4
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:44,000
I decide whether I completed it. MA does not pretend to grade pronunciation.

5
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Now the bundled restaurant scene sounds natural—and quickly becomes noise.

6
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:09,000
I tap Pause and help. MA stops its local tutor audio on that explicit tap.

7
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:24,000
This is one complete controlled segment, not an exact replay of what I heard.

8
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:39,000
MA turns that segment into a tiny Spanish repair lesson.

9
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Then I return to the same obligation: a restaurant table for one.

10
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:08,000
I try again without answer text and self-assess a fresh attempt.

11
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:22,000
The proof compares bounded facts, not a score or a claim of mastery.

12
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:39,000
The next step works locally. I can explicitly opt in to a GPT-5.6 recommendation.

13
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Only structured attempt facts leave the phone—never audio or a transcript.

14
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:58,000
I built the teacher I needed for when real Japanese becomes noise.
